<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="128" type="pollen">
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="128">Pollen.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="128">
trizonocolpate to pantocolpate, radially symmetrical, isopolar with circular or convex-quadrangular contour in polar view. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="128">Shape</emphasis>
: prolate-spheroidal (P/E=1.04-1.12). 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="128">Apertures</emphasis>
: 3 or 12, brevicolpate to colpate; polar area medium-sized to large (PAI=0.41-0.60). 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="128">Measurements</emphasis>
: pollen grains large to very large, (50.9)77.50(100.2) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(66.79)82.21(100.86) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in equatorial view; exine thickness (2.29)2.96(3.77) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="128">Ornamentation</emphasis>
: smooth surface with tectum perforate, ornated with spinules of (1.12)1.48(1.82) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
length 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(1.13)1.44(1.91) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
diameter in base; perforations (0.17)0.29(0.50) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in diameter (
